title: Galaxy advance in CONCACAF Champions League
text:
. View photo
Los Angeles Galaxy head coach Bruce Arena before an MLS soccer match against the San Jose Earthquakes, Friday, July 17, 2015, in Carson, Calif. (AP Photo/Jae C. Hong) PORT-OF-SPAIN, Trinidad (AP) -- Alan Gordon scored in the 82nd minute and the Los Angeles Galaxy tied Central FC 1-1 on Wednesday night to wrap a spot in the CONCACAF Champions League quarterfinals.
Los Angeles improved to 2-0-1 with one Group E game left Oct. 21 at Comunicaciones of Guatemala. The Galaxy routed Central 5-1 on Aug. 6 in California.
Gordon ended Los Angeles' goal drought across all competitions at 361 minutes.
Willis Plaza scored for Central (1-2-1) in the second minute.
The Galaxy left their entire regular starting lineup home. They started only three players - Baggio Husidic , Mika Vayrynen and Dan Gargan - with 10 or more MLS starts this season.
Comunicaciones is 1-2-0.
